{"ROLE":[{"def":"A part, or character, performed by an actor in a drama; hence, a part of function taken or assumed by any one; as, he has now taken the rôle of philanthropist.","pos":""}],"ROLL":[{"def":"To apply (one line or surface) to another without slipping; to bring all the parts of (one line or surface) into successive contact with another, in suck manner that at every instant the parts that have been in contact are equal.","pos":""}],"ROLLABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being rolled.","pos":""}],"ROLLER":[{"def":"One of series of long, heavy waves which roll in upon a coast, sometimes in calm weather.","pos":""},{"def":"A cylinder coated with a composition made principally of glue and molassess, with which forms of type are inked previously to taking an impression from them.","pos":""}],"ROLLER BEARING":[{"def":"A bearing containing friction rollers.","pos":""}],"ROLLER COASTER":[{"def":"An amusement railroad in which cars coast by gravity over a long winding track, with steep pitches and ascents.","pos":""}],"ROLLEY":[{"def":"A small wagon used for the underground work of a mine.","pos":""}],"ROLLIC":[{"def":"To move or play in a careless, swaggering manner, with a frolicsome air; to frolic; to sport; commonly in the form rollicking.","pos":""},{"def":"A kind of sausage, made in a bag of tripe, sliced and fried, famous among the Dutch of New Amsterdam and still known, esp.","pos":""}],"ROLLING":[{"def":"Rotating on an axis, or moving along a surface by rotation; turning over and over as if on an axis or a pivot; as, a rolling wheel or ball.","pos":""},{"def":"Moving on wheels or rollers, or as if on wheels or rollers; as, a rolling chair.","pos":""}],"ROLLING-PIN":[{"def":"A cylindrical piece of wood or other material, with which paste or dough may be rolled out and reduced to a proper thickness.","pos":""}],"ROLLWAY":[{"def":"A place prepared for rolling logs into a stream.","pos":""}],"ROLLY-POLY":[{"def":"A kind of pudding made of paste spread with fruit, rolled into a cylindrical form, and boiled or steamed.","pos":""},{"def":"Shaped like a rolly-poly; short and stout.","pos":""}],"ROLLY-POOLY":[{"def":"A game in which a ball, rolling into a certain place, wins.","pos":""}]}